# This file tells Git to store all .pdf files using Git LFS (Large File
# Storage) instead of committing their raw bytes directly into the repo's
# history. LFS stores a small "pointer" file in git and keeps the actual
# binary content in a separate LFS storage backend.
#
# Why this matters for RailAI: some of your PDFs (e.g. the 41MB ACTM file
# and the 24MB Electrical Reference Manual) are large. Without LFS, every
# clone of this repo would have to download the full PDF history, and
# GitHub's per-file soft limits (recommended <50MB) would eventually bite
# you as more PDFs are added.
#
# "filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text" is the standard incantation Git LFS
# uses to intercept these files during add/commit/checkout operations.
*.pdf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
